The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | All eyes on Kalpana
                                                                                                                                                                                                     All eyes on Kalpana
            OUR CORRESPONDENT                      
	Guwahati: It will be a testing bout for local favourite Kalpana Choudhury, when she takes on defending champion Ri Jong Hyang of DPR Korea in the light flyweight (48kg) semi-finals in the ongoing 4th ASBC Asian Womens Boxing Championship at the Karmabir Nabin Chandra Bordoloi Indoor Stadium here on Saturday.         
	In all, there will be 21 bouts on Thursday, featuring seven Indians in the semi-finals. India also have three direct entries into the finals.                                                                                                                          
